cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the problem of checking whether a union of conjunctive regular path queries with inverses (UC2RPQs) is equivalent to a union of conjunctive queries (UCQ), which is a fundamental problem in database theory. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses techniques from logic and automata theory, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which could place it under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
